.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH ox-snapshot 1  "ox-snapshot " 
.SH NAME
ox\-snapshot \- Manage snapshots
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBox\-snapshot\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage snapshots
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
ox\-snapshot\-create(1)
Create a named snapshot of current workflow state
.TP
ox\-snapshot\-list(1)
List all snapshots
.TP
ox\-snapshot\-diff(1)
Diff two snapshots, or a snapshot against current state
.TP
ox\-snapshot\-delete(1)
Delete a snapshot
.TP
ox\-snapshot\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
